She saved me.

00:02:31.610 --> 00:02:36.276
When I arrived in 6th grade, a known
criminal, the new teacher asked me

00:02:37.820 --> 00:02:42.286
to stay after school the first day,
she said I have heard about you.

00:02:44.460 --> 00:02:47.126
She was a tall woman,
with a deep crevice

00:02:47.570 --> 00:02:50.370
between her breasts
and a large, calm nose.

00:02:51.570 --> 00:02:54.236
She said, this is a
special library pass.

00:02:55.400 --> 00:02:59.000
As soon as you finish your
hour's work that hour's work

00:03:00.700 --> 00:03:01.276
that took ten minutes and then
the devil glanced into the room

00:03:04.190 --> 00:03:08.656
and found me empty, a house standing
open you can go to the library.

00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:16.493
Every hour I'd zip through the work
in a dash and slip out of my seat

00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:19.996
as if out of God's side and
sail down to the library,

00:03:20.970 --> 00:03:25.103
solo through the empty powerful
halls, flash my pass and stroll

00:03:27.340 --> 00:03:31.740
over to the dictionary to look up
the most interesting word I knew,

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:38.240
spank, dipping two fingers into
the jar of library paste to suck

00:03:40.100 --> 00:03:42.700
that tart mucilage
as I came to the page

00:03:44.270 --> 00:03:44.353
with the cocker spaniel's
silks curling

00:03:46.720 --> 00:03:49.053
up like the fine steam of the body.

00:03:51.830 --> 00:03:56.363
After spank, and breast, I'd move
on to Abe Lincoln and Helen Keller,

00:03:58.840 --> 00:04:02.973
safe in their goodness till the
bell, thanks to Mrs. Krikorian,

00:04:04.710 --> 00:04:07.110
amiable giantess with the kind eyes.

00:04:08.740 --> 00:04:13.206
When she asked me to write a play,
and direct it, and it was a flop,

00:04:16.370 --> 00:04:20.103
and I hid in the coat-closet,
she brought me a candy-cane

00:04:23.120 --> 00:04:23.360
as you lay a peppermint on the
tongue, and the worm will come

00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:28.880
up out of the bowel to get it.

00:04:31.320 --> 00:04:31.676
And so I was emptied of Lucifer and
filled with school glue and eros

00:04:35.430 --> 00:04:38.296
and Amelia Earhart,
saved by Mrs. Krikorian.

00:04:39.130 --> 00:04:41.330
And who had saved Mrs. Krikorian?

00:04:44.150 --> 00:04:44.273
When the Turks came across
Armenia, who slid her into the belly

00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:52.426
of a quilt, who locked her in a
chest, who mailed her to America?

00:04:54.200 --> 00:04:57.866
And that one, who saved her,
and that one who saved her,

00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:04.270
to save the one who saved Mrs.
Krikorian, who was standing there

00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:07.910
on the sill of 6th grade,
a wide-hipped angel,

00:05:10.830 --> 00:05:14.363
smoky hair standing up
weightless all around her head?

00:05:15.950 --> 00:05:19.750
I end up owing my soul to so
many, to the Armenian nation,

00:05:23.590 --> 00:05:28.056
one more soul someone jammed behind
a stove, drove deep into a crack

00:05:28.520 --> 00:05:30.520
in a wall, shoved under a bed.

00:05:33.530 --> 00:05:36.596
I would wake up, in the
morning, under my bed--

00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:42.613
