00:10:01.570 --> 00:10:05.103
&gt;&gt; Hi. Come Up From The
Fields Father by Walt Whitman.

00:10:08.410 --> 00:10:12.476
Come up from the fields father,
here's a letter from our Pete,

00:10:15.260 --> 00:10:19.793
and come to the front door mother,
here's a letter from thy dear son.

00:10:20.600 --> 00:10:24.533
Lo, 'tis autumn, Lo, where the
trees, deeper green, yellower

00:10:28.290 --> 00:10:32.690
and redder, Cool and sweeten Ohio's
villages with leaves fluttering

00:10:32.960 --> 00:10:37.626
in the moderate wind, Where apples
ripe in the orchards hang and grapes

00:10:38.040 --> 00:10:40.840
on the trellis'd vines,
Smell you the smell

00:10:41.080 --> 00:10:42.880
of the grapes on the vines?

00:10:43.160 --> 00:10:43.176
Smell you the buckwheat where
the bees were lately buzzing?

00:10:47.010 --> 00:10:51.076
Above all, lo, the sky so calm,
so transparent after the rain,

00:10:52.530 --> 00:10:57.196
and with wondrous clouds, Below too,
all calm, all vital and beautiful,

00:11:00.670 --> 00:11:02.470
and the farm prospers well.

00:11:03.600 --> 00:11:06.000
Down in the fields
all prospers well,

00:11:07.200 --> 00:11:11.466
but now from the fields come
father, come at the daughter's call,

00:11:13.800 --> 00:11:18.000
and come to the entry mother, to
the front door come right away.

00:11:19.650 --> 00:11:22.716
Fast as she can she
hurries, something ominous,

00:11:23.010 --> 00:11:25.543
her steps trembling,
She does not tarry

00:11:25.740 --> 00:11:28.206
to smooth her hair
nor adjust her cap.

00:11:28.940 --> 00:11:30.673
Open the envelope quickly.

00:11:32.100 --> 00:11:35.766
O this is not our son's
writing, yet his name is sign'd.

00:11:39.250 --> 00:11:43.650
O a strange hand writes for our
dear son, O stricken mother's soul!

00:11:46.700 --> 00:11:49.700
All swims before her
eyes, flashes with black,

00:11:50.610 --> 00:11:50.743
she catches the main words only.

00:11:52.610 --> 00:11:55.610
Sentences broken, gunshot
wound in the breast,

00:11:56.570 --> 00:11:58.970
cavalry skirmish, taken to hospital.

00:12:00.380 --> 00:12:02.980
At present low, but
will soon be better.

00:12:04.640 --> 00:12:06.706
Ah now the single figure to me.

00:12:08.270 --> 00:12:12.470
Amid all teeming and wealthy Ohio
with all its cities and farms.

00:12:12.730 --> 00:12:16.463
Sickly white in the face and
dull in the head very faint.

00:12:17.370 --> 00:12:20.970
By the jamb of a door leans
grieve not so, dear mother,

00:12:23.120 --> 00:12:23.773
the just-grown daughter
speaks through her sobs.

00:12:25.600 --> 00:12:29.333
The little sisters huddle
around speechless and dismay'd.

00:12:29.920 --> 00:12:33.986
See, dearest mother, the letter
says Pete will soon be better.

00:12:35.840 --> 00:12:39.506
Alas poor boy, he will never
be better, nor may-be needs

00:12:41.460 --> 00:12:44.126
to be better, that
brave and simple soul.

00:12:45.440 --> 00:12:49.106
While they stand at home at
the door he is dead already.

00:12:49.710 --> 00:12:51.110
The only son is dead.

00:12:52.430 --> 00:12:54.696
But the mother needs to be better.

00:12:57.070 --> 00:12:59.936
She with thin form
presently drest in black.

00:13:00.900 --> 00:13:02.700
By day her meals untouch'd,

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:07.000
then at night fitfully
sleeping, often waking.

00:13:08.200 --> 00:13:12.333
In the midnight waking, weeping,
longing with one deep longing.

00:13:13.690 --> 00:13:16.090
O that she might withdraw unnoticed,

00:13:17.160 --> 00:13:19.560
silent from life escape
and withdraw.

00:13:21.120 --> 00:13:24.320
To follow, to seek, to be
with her dear dead son.

